The proposed modification goes in the right direction of adding flexibility to tarmac delays rule. Its necessary to have more clarification on which will be the areas of the tarmac where the air carrier has control and how we will have the records of communication with the FAA control tower, airport authority, or other relevant authority directing the aircraft to prove there were efforts to manage the situation in the best possible way.

DOT should align the departure delay exception with the tarmac delay statute and without distinguishing control of the tarmac area;
The start of a tarmac delay for a departing flight should be a performance-based standard;
DOT should further improve tarmac delay reporting requirements;
DOT should defer to the safety and security determinations of the pilot-in-command; and
The Tarmac Delay Rule continues to impose significant costs and adverse impacts on consumers and the airlines
